Vintage technical illustration style: A detailed cross-section view of an intricate mechanical filing cabinet from the 1950s, rendered in sepia and muted amber tones. The cabinet's interior reveals an elaborate clockwork mechanism with brass gears, copper tubes, and rotating drums covered in tiny punch-card patterns. Multiple drawer compartments are shown at various angles, each containing miniature conveyor belts sorting colorful index cards into precise categories. Steam wisps curl from small pipes along the sides. The background features aged blueprint paper with faded grid lines and coffee stains. Tiny mechanical arms with magnifying glasses inspect each card as it passes through the sorting system. The overall mood is nostalgic yet industrious, capturing the essence of systematic data organization through an analog lens.
